President Obama has announced his intent to nominate R. David Harden as Assistant Administrator for Democracy, Conflict, and Humanitarian Assistance at the United States Agency for International Development (USAID). Harden is currently the Mission Director at the USAID Mission in the West Bank and Gaza and has extensive experience in various roles within USAID. 

Additionally, President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key Administration posts. Reverend Traci D. Blackmon will serve as a member of the President's Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. Blackmon is the Acting Executive Minister of Justice and Witness Ministries for The United Church of Christ and has a background in the healthcare industry. 

Rachel Held Evans will also be appointed as a member of the President's Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. Evans is a Christian blogger and author, known for her books such as "Faith Unraveled" and "A Year of Biblical Womanhood". 

Lastly, Reverend Adam Hamilton will serve as a member of the President's Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. Hamilton is the founding Pastor of the United Methodist Church of the Resurrection and is a well-known author and speaker on leadership.